---> Key Points to Remember
* Queue follows **FIFO**
* Enqueue â†’ Rear
* Dequeue â†’ Front
* Circular Queue solves space issue
* Queue is used when **order matters**

---> One-Line Definition (Perfect for Exams)
> **Queue is a linear data structure that follows FIFO principle where insertion happens at rear and deletion happens at front.**

